     <body>
     <div type="dedication">
   <head>TO HIS EVER-HONOVRED
LADY, MY LADY COVN<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tesse
of Montrois,
&amp;c.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>GReat is the worth of thy triumphing <hi>Fame,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>With <hi>Faith, Hope, Loue,</hi> in thy sweet soule in<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>shrind,</l>
      <l>A endlesse world shall eternise thy name,</l>
      <l>And crowne the glorious <hi>vertue</hi> of thy mind.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Thy feruent <hi>faith</hi> to Christ is so inclind,</l>
      <l>Which makes ritch <hi>hopes</hi> vp to the Heau'ns aspire</l>
      <l>From thence thy <hi>loue,</hi> descends in ruthfull kinde,</l>
      <l>And helps the poore in their distress'd desire.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Long may thou liue, and long may God aboue</l>
      <l>Increase, confirme, reward, <hi>faith, hope,</hi> and <hi>loue.</hi>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>S. GRAHAME.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
